arStrings.szText: I never wanted to be immortalized. Never wanted my words cited in the justification of wrongdoing. The Zakarum did all that, and worse.
But they were enabled by my loved onesâ€”my Dedicants. They made sure that when I died, I left behind much more than I intended. Words, images. This form I take now, even.
I think this room was built to honor them. And, though they betrayed me, though I should be angry...it gladdens me to see their faces, after all these years.
